ENJOY THE BEAUTIFUL OUTDOORS AT CASEY'S PLACE !
﻿
Welcome to Casey’s Place
After the beach or after a tiring day of shopping on Ocean drive (Vero's well known shopping district) Casey's place is sure to meet all of your
expectations. Tucked away on the corner of Cardinal and Azalea,  it is just steps away from the crashing blue waves and beautiful white sandy beaches that Vero Beach is known for.  Vero's
local beachside shops are a nearby hit too, with unique clothing, jewlery, home goods and even relaxing spas at your fingertips.
The finest hotels on the east coast can be also found. Within walking distance, the luxurious Vero Beach Hotel and Spa, the famous Driftwood resort
and Gloria and Emilio Estefan's premiere hotel Coste d' Este can be found, just to name a few.
Dining at Casey's is a unique and enjoyable experience.  We take walk up orders or Call in and pick ups.
If you were wondering, here's the process:
After the difficult decision of what mouthwatering item you would like, you place your order with the friendly girl at the register.  It will be
put under a name, and when it's ready your name will be called.  As you wait for your food, native palms, market umbrellas, and a historic oak tree surrounds you.
One trademark that makes Casey's Place so unique is not taking reservations.  During lunch rush, there are only so many tables but lots of
people; all seats are open.  You never know who you might be sharing a table with!  It could be a local resident or even an adventurous tourist.  A lot of revenue also comes from
businesses on the beach.  Brokers, bankers, contractors, attourneys and doctors are commonly seen. Even A-list celebrities stop by and dine at Casey's!
Whether you are craving an awesome lunch or looking to make new friends, Casey's Place is the place to be. So run on over to Casey's Place on the
corner of Cardinal and Azalea, you will surely enjoy it!
